and that's just

00:25:40.171 --> 00:25:41.920
going to slow things
down if you're trying

00:25:41.920 --> 00:25:43.300
to get a dance party started.

00:25:43.300 --> 00:25:43.960
ALEC LEE: Yeah!

00:25:43.960 --> 00:25:45.550
Dance party.

00:25:45.550 --> 00:25:47.710
ANTHONY CAPORALE: No, Alec.

00:25:47.710 --> 00:25:48.265
Alec.

00:25:48.265 --> 00:25:49.470
ALEC LEE: Come on, now.

00:25:49.470 --> 00:25:50.317
Here we go.

00:25:50.317 --> 00:25:51.070
Woo!

00:25:51.070 --> 00:25:51.570
Woo!

00:25:51.570 --> 00:25:52.528
ANTHONY CAPORALE: Alec.

00:25:52.528 --> 00:25:53.300
ALEC LEE: Woo!

00:25:53.300 --> 00:25:55.340
Yeah.

00:25:55.340 --> 00:25:57.880
ANTHONY CAPORALE: No,
he's very excited.

00:25:57.880 --> 00:25:59.485
We're not twerking yet.

00:25:59.485 --> 00:26:00.850
ALEC LEE: Oh, All right.

00:26:00.850 --> 00:26:01.540
I'll be back.

00:26:01.540 --> 00:26:04.410
ANTHONY CAPORALE: Good.

00:26:04.410 --> 00:26:06.440
All right.

00:26:06.440 --> 00:26:10.360
So alcohol is toxic to
microorganisms, right?

00:26:10.360 --> 00:26:13.630
But what makes alcohol?

00:26:13.630 --> 00:26:15.254
This was like five minutes ago.

00:26:15.254 --> 00:26:15.920
AUDIENCE: Yeast.

00:26:15.920 --> 00:26:16.210
ANTHONY CAPORALE: Yeah.

00:26:16.210 --> 00:26:16.709
Very good.

00:26:16.709 --> 00:26:17.490
Yeast.

00:26:17.490 --> 00:26:19.420
And what is yeast?

00:26:19.420 --> 00:26:22.100
A microorganism.

00:26:22.100 --> 00:26:23.610
There's the rub.

00:26:23.610 --> 00:26:26.950
You know, as any of you
that have kept fish,

00:26:26.950 --> 00:26:31.690
or have hamsters,
or children know,

00:26:31.690 --> 00:26:36.740
most things don't thrive
in their own excrement.

00:26:36.740 --> 00:26:39.220
Ditto yeast.

00:26:39.220 --> 00:26:41.080
See how our yeast is--

00:26:41.080 --> 00:26:43.140
whoa.

00:26:43.140 --> 00:26:44.379
Nicole, nicely done.

00:26:44.379 --> 00:26:45.670
NICOLE DIMATTEI: I made a mess.

00:26:45.670 --> 00:26:47.950
It's perfect.

00:26:47.950 --> 00:26:50.638
Let's give it up for yeast,
ladies and gentlemen.

00:26:50.638 --> 00:26:52.933
[APPLAUSE]

00:26:53.395 --> 00:26:55.895
ANTHONY CAPORALE: You're not
going to hear that at Hamilton.

00:26:59.090 --> 00:26:59.840
All right.

00:26:59.840 --> 00:27:02.540
That's not bad for-- that
was like, what, maybe 10

00:27:02.540 --> 00:27:04.340
minutes of fermentation?

00:27:04.340 --> 00:27:05.840
But as soon as the
alcohol builds up

00:27:05.840 --> 00:27:11.360
to a certain level, usually
not much more than about 15%,

00:27:11.360 --> 00:27:15.140
the yeast will either
go dormant or die.

00:27:15.140 --> 00:27:16.520
No more alcohol after that.

00:27:16.520 --> 00:27:21.740
Now this is why most fermented
drinks top out at about 17%

00:27:21.740 --> 00:27:23.420
ABV.

00:27:23.420 --> 00:27:27.050
Beer's generally
about 3% to 5% ABV.

00:27:27.050 --> 00:27:30.890
Cider hovers around 6%.

00:27:30.890 --> 00:27:32.740
Apples have more
sugar than grain,

00:27:32.740 --> 00:27:35.120
so cider ends up with
more alcohol than beer.

00:27:35.120 --> 00:27:37.630
And wine, which usually
starts with the most sugar,

00:27:37.630 --> 00:27:41.150
usually ends up at
between 10% and 15%.

00:27:41.150 --> 00:27:45.583
Any idea what the ABV of
a spirit like vodka is?

00:27:45.583 --> 00:27:46.470
AUDIENCE: 40.

00:27:46.470 --> 00:27:47.830
ANTHONY CAPORALE: 40, very good.

00:27:47.830 --> 00:27:51.400
So my question is, how do we
go from beer, with an alcohol

00:27:51.400 --> 00:27:57.280
content of 5%, to vodka, with
an alcohol content of 40,

00:27:57.280 --> 00:28:01.920
if we know the yeast is going
to give up the ghost at 15%?

00:28:01.920 --> 00:28:02.420
Say it.

00:28:02.420 --> 00:28:02.900
AUDIENCE: Distillation.

00:28:02.900 --> 00:28:04.610
ANTHONY CAPORALE: Distillation.

00:28:04.610 --> 00:28:06.470
Very good.

00:28:06.470 --> 00:28:08.880
So to find out how we came
up with that neat trick,

00:28:08.880 --> 00:28:11.330
you're going to have to come
see The Imbible at New World

00:28:11.330 --> 00:28:12.600
Stages.

00:28:12.600 --> 00:28:14.960
We are playing.

00:28:14.960 --> 00:28:16.388
Thank you very much.

00:28:16.388 --> 00:28:19.177
[APPLAUSE]

